description:
&lt;p&gt;Trinity Surgery&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Receptionist and Repeat Prescription Clerk Vacancy&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full Time 37.5 hours per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Plus holiday and sickness cover&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit a receptionist/ repeat prescription clerk to join our busy, friendly Practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate needs to be well-motivated and efficient; will possess good people skills and enjoy working in a busy environment. They must be able to communicate clearly and effectively and have the ability to work well within a determined team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Previous experience of working in a GP Practice, knowledge of the SystmOne clinical system, medical terminology, read coding and the Quality and Outcomes Framework (QoF) are advantageous; multi-lingual skills may be beneficial. Accuracy and attention to detail are essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reception responsibilities include assisting and directing patients in accessing the appropriate service or healthcare professional in a courteous, efficient and effective way whilst projecting a positive and friendly image to patients both in person and via the telephone; offering general assistance to the practice team and undertaking wide-ranging administrative duties to assist in the day to day running of the practice including the provision of clerical support to clinical staff and other members of the practice team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Repeat prescription duties include the processing of prescriptions accurately and in a timely manner in accordance with practice guidelines.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you possess the above qualities, are willing and eager to learn new skills and are flexible in your approach to work we would like to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
